Women#Name World Rank CR Points ABA Wins 2024 Christiane BILODEAU 170 349.05 5 Shantel KOENIG 192 359.06 2 Ella MYERS 196 359.77 1 Annie SCOTT 246 376.96 2 Susanne MCARTHUR 297 389.62 0 Men#Name World Rank CR Points ABA Wins 2024 Finn BORSTMAYER 408 224.08 5 Mark FAGNAN 449 228.13 2 Ryan MACLEAN 546 236.69 0 Andrew DAVIDSON 571 238.01 1 Sean GERMAINE 699 247.54 1 Running up that hill - photo by Agniewska. I spent most of the race following a dude (in red in the picture). In the fifth (&amp; final) lap when we had to get off our bikes and carry them up a super steep grassy hill I got past him. Usually I pass people going uphill and then they pass me on the flatter parts but I was feeling good and was all, &ldquo;I can&rsquo;t let him take that back!&rdquo; I managed the steep downhill that followed the runup and made it up the next climb smoothly. Amazingly (for me), I actually had enough left in me to keep the power down through the rest of the corners and flat bits and the barriers the rest of the way to the finish, like half a lap.&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
Also known as a Le Mans Start.&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;
Sidney MCGILL and Nico KNOLL are our actual best best racers (ranked 31 and 151 in the world respectively as of this writing), but they haven&rsquo;t raced in ABA races this year, having bigger fish to fry.&#160;&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;

